node_9.description: This is Iris Chang's plan for Monday February 13: 7:00 am - Wake up and complete morning routine, freshen up, and have breakfast., 8:00 am - Attend morning classes at Oak Hill College, focusing on subjects of interest and engaging in quiet observations of the new male student., 12:00 pm - Have lunch with Mina and discuss the day ahead, including any thoughts on the new male student., 1:00 pm - Attend afternoon classes, participating thoughtfully while taking notes and absorbing information., 4:00 pm - Visit the library for an hour to study and conduct research for upcoming assignments., 5:00 pm - Head back to the dormitory and relax, enjoying some light reading before dinner., 6:00 pm - Have dinner with Mina and some friends; engage in light conversation while continuing to observe the dynamics in the group, especially regarding the new male student., 7:30 pm - Participate in a study group with classmates to prepare for upcoming exams, sharing insights when prompted but mostly listening., 9:00 pm - Go for a quiet walk around campus to reflect on the day and gather thoughts about her aspirations, friendships, and considering the possibilities with the new male student., 10:00 pm - Wind down for the night, journal her thoughts and desires about exploring a relationship, before preparing for bed., 11:00 pm - Go to sleep..
